{
  "id": "musescore3_compose_16bar_leadsheet",
  "app": "musescore3",
  "task": "MuseScore 3 is already open with /home/user/Documents/moonlight_scaffold.mscz — a single Piano part in G major (1 sharp), 3/4 time, 16 measures of whole-measure rests, current tempo quarter = 90 BPM, Work Title 'Untitled Score', empty Composer, no chord symbols, no lyrics.\n\nCompose and annotate a 16-measure lead sheet in place, then export as MusicXML:\n\n- Set Work Title to exactly 'Moonlight Waltz' and Composer to exactly 'Claire Dubois'.\n- Change the first tempo marking to exactly 108 BPM (quarter = 108).\n- Fill every measure with exactly three quarter notes (48 notes total), staying diatonic in G major; specific pitches are your choice.\n- Add a chord symbol above the downbeat of each measure, one per measure from m1 to m16, in this exact order: m1=G, m2=D, m3=Em, m4=C, m5=G, m6=D, m7=G, m8=G, m9=Em, m10=C, m11=G, m12=D, m13=Em, m14=Am, m15=D7, m16=G.\n- Add lyrics under the first 9 notes (the first three measures only), in this exact order: 'Moon', 'light', 'waltz', 'be', 'neath', 'the', 'stars', 'so', 'bright'.\n- Save in place at /home/user/Documents/moonlight_scaffold.mscz.\n- Export an Uncompressed MusicXML to exactly /home/user/Documents/moonlight_waltz.musicxml.\n\nAfter saving, workTitle must be 'Moonlight Waltz', composer must be 'Claire Dubois', first tempo must be 108 BPM, time signature must still be 3/4, key signature must still be 1 sharp, and the score must have 16 measures with at least 48 notes. All 16 chord symbols must appear at the specified measures, each of the 9 listed syllables must appear as lyric text, and the MusicXML export at /home/user/Documents/moonlight_waltz.musicxml must have exactly 1 part.",
  "env": {
    "files": [
      {
        "filename": "moonlight_scaffold.mscz",
        "sandbox_path": "/home/user/Documents/moonlight_scaffold.mscz"
      }
    ]
  },
